## Public Member Functions

### forallUnderlyingObjects() {#a0f65cc64b4f1f5d82ca7055c8cc7eb7d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>virtual bool llvm::AAUnderlyingObjects::forallUnderlyingObjects (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function-ref">function&#95;ref</a>&lt; bool(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &amp;)&gt; Pred, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/aa/#ac85851126814105f4a92b699293e4141">AA::ValueScope</a> Scope=<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/aa/#ac85851126814105f4a92b699293e4141ab563ef74be13fcdcf264798ed6af5666">AA::Interprocedural</a>) const</>}>
<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/check">Check</a> <code>Pred</code> on all underlying objects in <code>Scope</code> collected so far.

This method will evaluate <code>Pred</code> on all underlying objects in <code>Scope</code> collected so far and return true if <code>Pred</code> holds on all of them.
